The paper deals with combinatorial structures and extremal functions related to pattern avoidance, which are central topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of the formation width function and its relation to the maximum length of a sequence that avoids a pattern suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). The study of subsequences and pairwise distinct letters also points to a possible connection to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
